===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|citizen}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|lang=nfr|citesain||[[burgher]]; [[city]]-[[dweller]]}} &c., probably a variant of {{term|lang=nfr|cithein}} under influence of {{term|lang=nfr|deinzein||[[denizen]]}}, from {{etyl|xno}} and {{etyl|fro}} {{term|lang=fro|citeain}} &c. and {{term|lang=fro|citaien|}} &c. ("[[burgher]]"; modern French {{term|citoyen|lang=fr}}), from {{term|cite|lang=fro}} ("[[settlement]]; [[cathedral city]], [[city]]"; modern French {{term|cité|lang=fr}}) + {{term|-ain|lang=fro}} or {{term|-ien||[[-an]], [[-ian]]|lang=fro}}. ''See'' '''{{term|city#Etymology|city}}''' and '''{{term|hewe#Etymology|hewe}}'''.

